
JAN. 14, 2018

Dr. Idris Eleanor Leppla and Justin Benjamin Shubow are to be married Jan. 14 at Congregation Emanu-El in San Francisco. Rabbi Helen Cohn is to officiate.
The bride, 32, is a fourth-year psychiatric resident at Johns Hopkins Hospital in Baltimore. She graduated magna cum laude from Barnard College and received a medical degree from the University of California, Irvine.
She is the daughter of Jacquelyn K. Leppla and Bruce W. Leppla of San Francisco. The bride’s father is a partner in the San Francisco office of Lieff, Cabraser, Heimann & Bernstein, a law firm in New York. Her mother is a special-education teacher at Bowditch Middle School in Foster City, Calif.
The groom, 40, is the president of the National Civic Art Society, a nonprofit group promoting public art and architecture, in Washington. He graduated, magna cum laude, from Columbia and received a master’s degree in philosophy from the University of Michigan and a law degree from Yale.
He is the son of Lisa J. Shubow and Charles G. Shubow of Owings Mills, Md. The groom’s mother retired as a special-education physical education teacher at Claremont High School in Baltimore. His father is an administrative judge at the Equal Employment Opportunity Commission in Washington.
The groom’s previous marriage ended in divorce.
The couple were introduced by the groom’s parents in 2015 in Baltimore.
